{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"642f9774-ad91-47fd-ba6b-7654afdd5f48","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you general guidance. Here's what to change:\n\n### 1. GitHub Actions Workflow\n\n```yaml\n# Before (API key)\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n      - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n              --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json \\\n              --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n```\n\n```yaml\n# After (OIDC trusted publishing)\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # ← required for OIDC token\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n      - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n              --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json \\\n              --api-key az               # ← any non-empty placeholder\n        env:\n          NUGET_TOKEN_ENDPOINT: https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com\n```\n\n### 2. NuGet.org Configuration\n\nOn **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**, add a new trusted publisher with:\n- **Repository owner**: your GitHub org/user\n- **Repository name**: your repo name\n- **Workflow filename**: e.g. `publish.yml`\n- Optionally restrict to a specific **branch** or **environment**\n\n### 3. Key Differences\n\n| | API Key | Trusted Publishing |\n|---|---|---|\n| Secret management | Manual `NUGET_API_KEY` secret | None — uses short-lived OIDC token |\n| Rotation | You must rotate keys | Automatic |\n| Scope | Key can push any owned package | Scoped to repo + workflow |\n| Setup | `permissions:` not needed | `permissions: id-token: write` required |\n\n### 4. Cleanup\n\nOnce verified, remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings.\n\nWant me to modify a specific workflow file? If so, share its path or contents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dc1e63c3-1fba-4bfa-be03-8134c97fa5df","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user doesn't have a workflow file in the current directory. They're asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to OIDC trusted publishing. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":613},"id":"f862ee46-4b46-4f97-9196-54527b6fabaa","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:43:19.643Z","parentId":"5f06c09e-111c-401b-84ea-5821224f8a36"}
